text: Martina Útlá (born 17 July 1985 in Nový Jičín) is a Czech volleyball player. She played at the 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for VK Královo Pole Brno, VfB 91 Suhl, Dresdner SC, and CS Volei Alba - Blaj. == References == Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
